Ba Van Nguyen piloted a military helicopter to save his family during the fall of Saigon on April 30, 1975 . 
  Nguyen was able to fly his family out of the city and into the South China Sea where they were saved by the USS Kirk . 
  He managed to pilot the helicopter while getting out of his flight suit and jumping from the helicopter just seconds before it crashed . 
  He was reunited with the crew in 2009 and awarded a bravery medal for his bravery . 
 